{"cursor":"2562","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Bob Boilen' is the current host and the creator of NPR's online music show\n[[All Songs Considered]]. He is also the creator of the [http://www.npr.org/series/tiny-desk-\nconcerts/ Tiny Desk Concert] series for [http://www.npr.org/music/ NPR Music],\nhosting intimate performances at his desk. The series curated by Boilen and the\nteam of NPR Music was inspired by a comment made by NPR Music's Stephen Thompson\nwhen he jokingly invited musician Laura Gibson to perform at Bob's desk. The two\nof them went to see Gibson at a show at SXSW in 2008 and the loud crowd made it\nimpossible to hear her. The name of the series is a play on the name\n[http://www.bobboilen.info/music/Tiny_Desk_Unit.html Tiny Desk Unit] a band\nBoilen played in from 1979-1981. Bob Boilen was the director of the NPR show\n[[All Things Considered]] (1989â2007) and chose the music between the news\nstories for that show. Those musical snippets or \"buttons\" was the starting\npoint for the creation of All Songs Considered.\n\nBob Boilen writes music with electronics and friend Michael Barron; [http:/-\n/www.michaelbarron.info/Michael_Barron_Music_%26_Art/home.html home ] both were founding members of the psychedelic dance\nband [http://www.tinydeskunit.com Tiny Desk Unit] (1979â1981), for which Boilen\nplayed synthesizer. Boilen continues to write music with Michael Barron in a\nband called [http://www.bobboilen.info/music/Danger_Painters.html Danger\nPainters] and also writes and releases solo music. Boilen also composed the\noriginal theme music for [[Talk of the\nNation]]. [http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=2100252 Bob\nBoilen, NPR Biography] From 1982 to 1986 Boilen filled a variety of roles\nincluding composer with Baltimore's Impossible Theater, where he met and\ncollaborated with his wife and companion of 27 years, Laurie Stepp. He has also\nworked as a producer for Channel 50, and produced [[Science Live]] for the\nDiscovery Channel.\n","linknr":188,"url":"Bob_Boilen","recorded":1375078358,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Bob_Boilen&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Bob_Boilen&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/All_Songs_Considered","http://www.npr.org/series/tiny-desk-concerts/","http://www.npr.org/music/","/wiki/Stephen_Thompson_(producer)","/wiki/Laura_Gibson","http://www.bobboilen.info/music/Tiny_Desk_Unit.html","/wiki/NPR","/wiki/All_Things_Considered","#cite_note-1","http://www.tinydeskunit.com","http://www.bobboilen.info/music/Danger_Painters.html","/wiki/Talk_of_the_Nation","#cite_note-2","/wiki/Baltimore","/w/index.php?title=Impossible_Theater&action=edit&redlink=1","/w/index.php?title=Science_Live&action=edit&redlink=1","/wiki/Discovery_Channel","/w/index.php?title=Bob_Boilen&action=edit&section=1","#cite_ref-1","http://www.michaelbarron.info/Michael_Barron_Music_%26_Art/home.html","#cite_ref-2","http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=2100252","/w/index.php?title=Bob_Boilen&action=edit&section=2","http://www.bobboilen.info/","/wiki/Template:NPR","/wiki/Template_talk:NPR","//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:NPR&action=edit","/wiki/NPR","/wiki/All_Things_Cons